## Change 3: Pricing Section — Remove Hourly Rate

### What to change
The current pricing card prominently displays `$125/hr` as the primary number. This directly contradicts the business model, which is task/project-based — clients never see a rate, they see a project price. Remove the hourly rate and replace with messaging that reflects the actual model.

### What to remove
- The "HOURLY RATE" label
- The `$125/hr` number
- "One rate. Everything included." subtext

### What to replace it with
In the same left-column position where the rate currently sits, use:

```
HOW PRICING WORKS

You see a project price.
Not an hourly rate.

One flat number for the specific work — 
reviewed and approved before anything starts.
```

- "HOW PRICING WORKS" in the same small-caps muted label style
- "You see a project price. / Not an hourly rate." as the primary statement — Lora serif, sized similarly to how `$125/hr` was displayed, white text on the dark card
- The supporting sentence in smaller DM Sans, muted white/light tone, matching the existing descriptor text style

### What stays the same
The three right-column items remain unchanged:
- "Calls and advice are always free"
- "Scoped and approved before anything starts"
- "No surprises, ever"

The "HOW IT WORKS" three-step section (01/02/03) below inside the same card also remains unchanged.

The card layout, background color, border radius, and all other visual properties remain unchanged.

